						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in front of the Koṇḍasingappa(Narasimha) temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1347, Viśvāvasu, Vaiśākha, śu. 2, Friday, corresponding to 1425 A.D., May 19. However the week day was Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of <hi rend="italic">Upajagati</hi> in the temple of Narasiṁhadēva on the hill by Malli-seṭṭi, for the merit of his master Tammā-Nāyaniṅgāru.</p>						

						</summary>
